  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] A few Polish people, who'd managed to get out one way or another, came back in as interpreters.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of course, the Czechs, who usually can speak three or four languages, we usually-- we had quite a few Czechs who we recruited and used.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This commander that you saw last night, whose name escapes me right now, who was at the Nuremberg reunion, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was head of the Language Division.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he had had experiences in languages, and he immediately got hold of some top people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then Lieutenant Dostert, D-O-S-T-E-R-T, was the person who helped install the simultaneous translation equipment, simultaneous interpretation equipment, which had been furnished by IBM.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There's a story about that which may interest you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The initial plan had been to have interpreters who would have to sit and listen to each sentence or phrase spoken and interpret in the other language.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There'd be a pause while this was being done, and then the speaker could go on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This would be-- take a lot of time and, of course, it would have slowed the proceedings down a great deal.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But someone from IBM had been-- had furnished some linguistic mechanisms whereby a speaker could speak into an autophone, and it would be carried to another translator who would then speak the same thing in a different language as closely as he could.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this would be recorded and-- or available in that language.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Charlie Horsky, who I think you've interviewed, was back in Washington as the-- one of the early representatives of Justice Jackson, and he heard about this.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he actually cabled to Justice Jackson that he thought it might be worth trying.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Jackson immediately said, by all means, work on it.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
